[src:functional-equations/gamma-function-p01] The definition for the gamma function due to Weierstrass is also valid for all complex numbers z except non-positive integers: $\Gamma (z)={\frac {e^{-\gamma z}}{z}}\prod _{n=1}^{\infty }\left(1+{\frac {z}{n}}\right)^{-1}e^{z/n},$ where $\gamma \approx 0.577216$ is the EulerŌĆōMascheroni constant.
[src:functional-equations/gamma-function-p01] This is the Hadamard product of $\textstyle {\frac {1}{\Gamma (z)}}$ in a rewritten form.
