[src:functional-equations/riemann-zeta-function] The Riemann zeta function also appears in a form similar to the Mellin transform in an integral over the GaussŌĆōKuzminŌĆōWirsing operator acting on *x**s*ŌłÆ1; that context gives rise to a series expansion in terms of the falling factorial.
